{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7279fe45-4265-4504-b910-5f7d71d355bc","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` **natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a bridge for .NET 9 and earlier; it's no longer needed.\n\nYour project just needs `EnableMSTestRunner` (which you already have). I'll remove the obsolete property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01BF6ftyRB1Kx4wEmAmoEDwh","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-ed782a8cdf424f598dc88d0fb6a7677c/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-ed782a8cdf424f598dc88d0fb6a7677c/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"1b1e042a-9e54-49a4-a049-5d508d0ff399","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) via `EnableMSTestRunner`. They have `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to `true`.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. Starting with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` uses MTP by default when it detects an MTP-based test project. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a bridge for .NET 9 and earlier SDKs.\n \nFor .NET 10 specifically, `EnableMSTestRunner` is still required to make the test project an executable using MTP, but `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` can be safely removed since the SDK handles MTP natively.","outputTokens":724,"requestId":"67C9:2FF63B:2A850FD:2EDEC03:69FD3628"},"id":"7fb5df06-a6ca-432e-9252-18b2cb4420f2","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:02:45.952Z","parentId":"47ba9274-1c35-4ec3-8e9c-4393fb4dd25d"}
