{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9857437f-6554-451c-914d-198a6e8dae34","content":"**Summary:**\n\n- **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`** — removed. .NET 10's `dotnet test` detects MTP test executables natively; this property is only needed for .NET 9 SDK.\n- **`EnableMSTestRunner`** — keep it. This tells MSTest to produce an MTP-based executable, which is what `dotnet test` in .NET 10 expects.\n- **`OutputType Exe`** — keep it. Required for the MTP runner model.\n\nThat's all you need. Running `dotnet test` on .NET 10 SDK will automatically use the Microsoft.Testing.Platform protocol with your project as-is.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1b1e042a-9e54-49a4-a049-5d508d0ff399","outputTokens":162,"requestId":"67C4:13C959:2964EB6:2DC1903:69FD3637"},"id":"5a82d547-1fc2-4ae1-a698-152e32111d42","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:02:52.514Z","parentId":"8c4142a5-c964-498a-99c8-1f3bf2d519eb"}
